Former Mukurweini Member of Parliament Kabando wa Kabando has announced that he will be contesting for the Nyeri Senatorial seat in the upcoming August 2022 elections. The veteran politician said the decision to contest for the Senate seat came after "wide consultations and grassroots surveys." "Upon wide consultations, urgings, online & grassroots surveys and my spirit to so serve, I offer myself to be Senator of the Great County of NYERI. #KKCampaign will communicate details of this noble venture in 3 weeks. I pledge Clean Decent Issues Campaign," he said in a tweet on Thursday. Kabando will be seeking to unseat current senator Ephraim Maina and will be facing off with other aspirants including Wambugu Nyamu and business guru Dan Wamahiu who is taking a second stab at the position.